Johannesburg – The 2022 African Cup of Nations will kick off this coming weekend, starting with the African giants from the West of Africa, Cameroon (the hosts) will face off Burkina Faso on Sunday, 09 January at 18:00. Both national teams are in the Group A of the tournament, and the next match for the group will be Ethiopia vs Cape Verde which will play at 21:00. This will mark the very first matches of the 52 games set to be played until the last leg in February, where the winner for the Afcon 2022 will be announced. The complete 52-match schedule for the African Cup of Nations (Afcon)  to be held in Cameroon from 9 January to 6 February 2022 is as follows: Group  A Sunday, 9 January Cameroon v Burkina Faso – 18:00 Cape Verde v Ethiopia – 21:00 Thursday, 13 January Cameroon v Ethiopia – 18:00 Burkino Faso v Cape Verde – 21:00 Monday, 17 January Cameroon v Cape Verde – 18:00 Burkino Faso v Ethiopia – 18:00 Group B Monday, 10 January Senegal v Zimbabwe – 15:00 Guinea v Malawi – 18:00 Friday, 14 January Guinea v Senegal – 15:00 Malawi v Zimbabwe – 16:00 Tuesday, 18 January Malawi v Senegal – 18:00 Guinea v Zimbabwe,– 18:00 Group C Sunday, 10 January Ghana v Morocco – 18:00 Comoros v Gabon – 21:00 Friday, 14 January Comoros v Morocco – 18:00 Gabon v Ghana – 21:00 Tuesday, 18 January Gabon v Morocco – 21:00 Comoros v Ghana, Garoua – 21:00 Group D Tuesday, 11 January Egypt v Nigeria – 18:00 Guinea-Bissau v Sudan – 21:00 Saturday, 15 January Nigeria v Sudan – 18:00 Egypt v Guinea Bissau – 21:00 Wednesday, 19 January Guinea Bissau v Nigeria – 21:00 Egypt v Sudan – 21:00 Group E Tuesday, 11 January Algeria v Sierra Leone – 15:00 Wednesday, 12 January Equatorial Guinea v Ivory Coast – 21:00 Sunday, 16 January Ivory Coast v Sierra Leone – 18:00 Algeria v Equatorial Guinea – 21:00 Thursday, 20 January Algeria v Ivory Coast – 18:00 Equatorial Guinea v Sierra Leone – 18:00 Group F Wednesday, 12 January Mali v Tunisia – 15:00 Gambia v Mauritania – 18:00 Sunday, 16 January Gambia v Mali – 15:00 Mauritania v Tunisia – 18:00 Thursday, 20 January Gambia v Tunisia – 21:00 Mali v Mauritania – 21:00 Round of 16 The round of 16 will see two teams that will come first and in second position from their respective groups. The first match of the round of 16 will be played on Sunday, 23 January, until 26 January. Quarter-finals The quarter-finals will be played on 29 January and 30 January. Semi-finals The semi-finals will take place on Wednesday, 2 February, and Thursday, 3 February. Third place Sunday, 6 February Losing semi-finalists Final The final of Afcon will play on Sunday, 6 February at 21:00. For the latest sports news from Sunday World, click here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.